      <textAnnotation id="sid-DA4AED8B-C742-411F-912C-DF6499AA101E" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Exception scenario: This is an L3 component. It is shown here to depict the continuity of flow</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-5142449E-CE8F-4199-A6C9-1C1383926255" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Process Tower: PTP - Procure To Pay
Process Group: PM - Procure Materials and Services (Direct &amp; Indirect)
Process: PM-080-130 Select New Supplier &amp; Reissue PO
</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-70C12645-BA26-485D-B3ED-7C503C2CB1EA" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Note: 
1. Cluster Definitions:
   a) Cluster 1: Materials and Indirect Procurement (Fab, Spares, AT, SIMs, Equipment materials and Indirect)
   b) Cluster 2: Subcontracting (OSAT, Foundry, ODM, Box CPU)
   c) Cluster 3: Capital and Construction (Construction, Equipment)
2. This process is applicable for all 3 clusters</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-79E7A54F-4199-4E8A-907E-DEADCB93554E" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-left"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-right"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Flow has been migrated to BIC. Please inform the process steward Nageswaran, Rohan &lt;rohan.nageswaran@intel.com&gt; and BPM Champions D'Elia, Traci &lt;traci.delia@intel.com&gt;,Newman, Jennifer &lt;jennifer.newman@intel.com&gt;of any design changes that occur within the flow moving forward. This will enable us to reflect those changes in the BIC and WIKI business process documentation.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
